Champagne is a blend of wines from white and black. grapes grown on the rolling hillsides of the Marne Valley northeast of Paris. (Occasionally, a Champagne is made entirely from white grapes, when it is called a blanc de blancs; or from black grapes,

when tt is called a blane de noirs).

For assurance of quality we must look to the skill and integrity of the makers, whether small individual proprietors or the world-famous Champagne firms, whose reputations are built on the great wines to which they proudly attach their names.
